8 (2) Upon the presentation to a governmental entity of a valid,
9 outstanding protection order pursuant to the Protection Orders Act or the
10 Uniform Interstate Enforcement of Domestic Violence Protection Orders Act
11 or an immediate protective order issued under the Immediate Protection
12 from Abuse Act protecting the driver of a vehicle jointly registered with
13 or registered solely in the name of the individual against whom the order
14 was issued, captured plate data may not be disclosed except pursuant to a
15 disclosure order under subsection (2) of section 60-3205 or as the result
16 of a match pursuant to subsection (2) of section 60-3203.
17 Sec. 19. Original section 29-4315, Revised Statutes Cumulative
18 Supplement, 2024, and sections 26-102, 26-114, 28-311.04, 28-358.01,
19 28-1205, 28-1206, 29-2292, 42-927, and 60-3209, Revised Statutes
20 Supplement, 2025, are repealed.
